---
// Side-by-side fast vs slow powder visualization for a 13" PCC barrel.
// Hand-tuned widths express the burn-vs-expansion ratio narratively, not from data.
---
<figure class="barrel-diagram">
  <h3>13″ PCC Barrel: Gas pressure state when the bullet exits</h3>

  <div class="barrel-row">
    <div class="barrel-label fast">Fast<br />Powder</div>
    <div class="barrel-visual" aria-hidden="true" style="background: #1a2010;">
      <div
        class="barrel-burn"
        style="width: 26%; background: linear-gradient(90deg, #4ade80, #22c55e);"
      >
        BURN
      </div>
      <div
        class="barrel-expansion"
        style="left: 26%; right: 6px; background: repeating-linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(34,197,94,0.08) 0px, rgba(34,197,94,0.03) 8px, transparent 8px, transparent 16px);"
      >
        <span style="color: rgba(34,197,94,0.5);">← EXPANDING TOWARD ATMOSPHERIC →</span>
      </div>
      <div class="barrel-muzzle-zone" style="background: rgba(34,197,94,0.15);"></div>
      <div class="barrel-bullet">
        <div class="barrel-bullet-pip"></div>
        <div class="barrel-bullet-label">◀ BULLET</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="barrel-desc fast-desc">
      <strong style="color:var(--green);">Near atmospheric at muzzle</strong><br />
      10″ of expansion after burn<br />
      Gas is slow, cool, and quiet
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="barrel-row">
    <div class="barrel-label slow">Slow<br />Powder</div>
    <div class="barrel-visual" aria-hidden="true" style="background: #201010;">
      <div
        class="barrel-burn"
        style="width: 78%; background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ef4444, #f87171, #ef4444);"
      >
        ACTIVE COMBUSTION
      </div>
      <div
        class="barrel-expansion"
        style="left: 78%; right: 6px; background: rgba(239,68,68,0.08);"
      >
        <span style="color: rgba(239,68,68,0.5); font-size:9px;">tiny<br />gap</span>
      </div>
      <div class="barrel-muzzle-zone" style="background: rgba(239,68,68,0.6);"></div>
      <div class="barrel-bullet">
        <div class="barrel-bullet-pip"></div>
        <div class="barrel-bullet-label">◀ BULLET</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="barrel-desc slow-desc">
      <strong style="color:var(--red);">Far above atmospheric at muzzle</strong><br />
      Only 3″ of expansion after burn<br />
      Gas exits hot, fast, and loud
    </div>
  </div>

  <figcaption class="barrel-note">
    Both diagrams show the same instant: the bullet leaving the muzzle at 130 PF. The bullet
    position and speed are identical. What's different is the gas pressure behind it:
    near-atmospheric (quiet exit) vs far above atmospheric (violent exit).
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .barrel-diagram {
    margin: 32px 0;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 32px;
  }
  .barrel-diagram h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .barrel-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
    gap: 20px;
  }
  .barrel-row:last-of-type { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .barrel-label {
    width: 100px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    text-align: right;
  }
  .barrel-label.fast { color: var(--green); }
  .barrel-label.slow { color: var(--red); }

  .barrel-visual {
    flex: 1;
    height: 48px;
    position: relative;
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .barrel-burn {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; left: 0; bottom: 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
  }
  .barrel-expansion {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; bottom: 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }
  .barrel-muzzle-zone {
    position: absolute;
    top: -6px; bottom: -6px; right: -2px;
    width: 6px;
    border-radius: 0 3px 3px 0;
  }
  .barrel-bullet {
    position: absolute;
    right: -30px;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 2px;
  }
  .barrel-bullet-pip {
    width: 10px;
    height: 16px;
    background: var(--accent);
    border-radius: 2px 6px 6px 2px;
  }
  .barrel-bullet-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 9px;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 600;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .barrel-desc {
    width: 200px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin-left: 52px;
  }

  .barrel-note {
    margin-top: 16px;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .barrel-diagram { padding: 18px 16px; }
    .barrel-row { flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
    .barrel-label { width: 56px; font-size: 9px; }
    .barrel-visual { min-height: 40px; }
    .barrel-desc { width: 100%; margin-left: 0; font-size: 11px; }
    /* Decorative bullet pip + "EXPANDING TOWARD ATMOSPHERIC →" overflow at
       narrow widths. Hide them on mobile (the burn/expand color zones still
       carry the visual story). */
    .barrel-bullet { display: none; }
    .barrel-expansion span { display: none; }
  }
</style>
